summary:
The Security Council, recalling its previous resolutions on Côte d'Ivoire, particularly resolution 1727 (2006), and the Group of Experts' final report (S/2007/349), determines that the situation in Côte d'Ivoire remains a threat to international peace and security. Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter, it: 
1. Extends the Group of Experts' mandate, as set out in resolution 1727 (2006), until 31 October 2007, and requests the Secretary-General to take necessary administrative measures; 
2. Requests the Group to submit a written update to the Council, through the Committee established by resolution 1572 (2004), before 15 October 2007, on the implementation of measures imposed by resolutions 1572 (2004) and 1643 (2005); 
3. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
